<TABLE BORDER=0 cellpadding=4 border=0 cellspacing=1 WIDTH="95%"><TR bgcolor="#D5E6E1"><TD COLSPAN=2><CENTER><FONT SIZE="2" COLOR="#000080" FACE="Verdana, Arial">T O P I C  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; R E V I E W</font></CENTER></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">ToneDeaf</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">i play a lvl 31 ikkysaur monk (untwinked) and i have a few questions...  first off, i heard that monks are the only class that can bind wounds to 75%.  is this true and at what level does this happen?  my bind wound skill is up around 140 and i can still only bind to 50.<BR>second, i am wearing very heavy shoulder and face equipment.  both splitpaw hide i believe.  they have ok stat increases, but i'm trying to reduce my armor weight as much as possible so i can carry 2 backpacks and remain under 14...  does anyone know of any good equipment that i can hunt for and if so can give me a clue on how to get it?<BR>thanks in advance for any info you can provide =)<BR></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">taobob</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">With a Monk, you can still only use the Bind Wound skill up to 50%, just like all the other classes... The extra healing above the 50% comes from the Monk only skill of Mend.... Using you med skill can effectively heal you all the way from being near death to 75% of health....<P>You second question would depend on exactly what kind of stat increases you were looking for from the armor pieces. I would go and do an equipment search for light Monk type armor... I know that  <A HREF="http://everquest.allakhazam.com/" TARGET=_blank>Allakhazams</A>  has a really good items search by class, and maybe you could find light weaight equipment there that would be easy to get at your level...<p>[This message has been edited by taobob (edited 12-19-2000).]</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">ToneDeaf</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">thanks for the reply =)  it had occured to me that i could bind to 50 and then mend - that's my entire technique (and i'm sure i'm not the only one) for soloing as a monk...  i just heard somewhere that bind wounds could actually get you to 75 alone and that mend could get you to 100...<BR>as far as stat increases, i am going for agi and dex increases whenever possible as speed is a monk's strong point...  i have some crescent armor from many hours of hunting in dalnir, and i believe there is a shoulderpad piece somewhere but i don't know what it drops off of =(  as far as a mask, i have no idea what to get or where to get it...</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Caraen</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">as a monk..when your Bind wound skill reach 200 youll be able to bind wound to 70 % health then mend the rest<BR></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">loligo</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">A monk will bind wound to 50% until either level 50 or 51 (I think it's 51).  At that level, if the bind wound skill is at 201, the monk will be able to bind to the higher percentage. 201 and 51 (or 50?) are required.</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>
</FONT>
